HEADWORD: Megaphyton
<hw>Me*gaph"y*ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <grk>me`gas</grk> great + <grk>fyto`n</grk> plant.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of tree ferns with large,
two-ranked leaves, or fronds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

